<!-- ===============================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A sought-after western suburb where elevated blocks, established canopy and school catchments converge.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Chapel Hill sits approximately twelve kilometres west of the Brisbane CBD, on the elevated ridge that runs between Kenmore and Bardon. The suburb's defining characteristic is its relationship with the surrounding bushland: generous blocks with established eucalyptus canopy, properties that capture elevated outlooks across the western hinterland, and a streetscape that feels genuinely removed from the density of inner Brisbane despite sitting well within the urban boundary. It is the kind of suburb where families stay for decades once they arrive.
    </p>
